SUMMARY:Sonoma County Bluegrass & Folk Festival
DESCRIPTION:The Sonoma County Bluegrass & Folk Festival’s tradition of swinging above its weight in fun continues this year with another soul-stirring display of fine bluegrass and folk music. In addition to the on-stage attractions\, this festival is known for its hot picking scene\, so pack up your axe and get ready for a memorable celebration of community and music in Sebastopol! \nStage Schedule \n12:40 Pulso de Barro: Mesoamerican Sounds \n1:20 Jesse Appelman West Coast String Band \n2:25 Manning Music School \n3:15 Monroe Crossing \n4:20 Evie Ladin Band \n5:25 Five Mile Mountain Road \n6:35 Laurie Lewis and Nina Gerber \n7:50 Square Dance with KC Heil \nTimes are approximate and subject to change! Watch this page for additional details as they become available. \n$35-$50 (Ages 12 & under free) \nThe SCBFF is brought to you by the California Bluegrass Association\, with the help of the Sonoma County Folk Society and the Sebastopol Kiwanis Club. \n** Please note: This event is held at the Community Center\, but it is produced by the California Bluegrass Association.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/sonoma-county-bluegrass-folk-festival/
LOCATION:Sebastopol Community Cultural Center\, 390 Morris St\, Sebastopol\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Sonoma-County-Bluegrass-festival-2026-s.jpg
